description:
AutonomousMode:  Table recording the activation state and ID of autonomous modes for each cell in a given area at a specific time, including metadata about the data source and format.
dateTime: Timestamp of the record.
Area_Name: Geographical area where the cell is located.
CellId: Unique identifier of the cell site.
Id2: Redundant cell identifier (likely a duplicate of CellId).
Id3:  Ancillary identifier (purpose unclear from sample data).
Id4: Ancillary identifier (purpose unclear from sample data).
vsDataType: Type of data (identifies this as autonomous mode data).
vsDataFormatVersion: Version of the data format.
AutonomousMode.expiration: Expiration time of the autonomous mode configuration (currently empty in sample data).
AutonomousMode.activationState: Current activation state of the autonomous mode (e.g., ACTIVE, INACTIVE).
AutonomousMode.autonomousModeId: Unique identifier of the specific autonomous mode configuration.
queries: Show me all AutonomousMode entries where activationState is ACTIVE and Area_Name is 'Downtown'.
What is the vsDataFormatVersion for AutonomousMode records in Area_Name 'Suburbia' between 10 AM and 11 AM on October 26th, 2024?
Retrieve all CellId values with AutonomousMode.activationState = INACTIVE and a dateTime before 2024-10-27 00:00:00.
How many distinct AutonomousMode.autonomousModeId values exist for Area_Name = 'Airport' with a vsDataType of 'AutonomousMode'?
Find all records where Id3 and Id4 are not NULL and AutonomousMode.activationState changed from ACTIVE to INACTIVE since yesterday.
